HEADWORD: Fructify
<hw>Fruc"ti*fy</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ucr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>fructifier</ets>, L. <ets>fructificare</ets>;
<ets>fructus</ets> fruit + <ets>-ficare</ets> (only in comp.), akin to
L. <ets>facere</ets> to make. See <er>Fruit</er>, and
<er>Fact</er>.]</ety> <def>To bear fruit.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Causeth the earth
to <xex>fructify</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beveridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

